pageContext.claim: “Congratulations to Mike Dewine on his big win in the Great State of Ohio. He will be a great Governor with a heavy focus on HealthCare and Jobs.  His Socialist opponent in November should not do well, a big failure in last job!”
pageContext.analysis: Mike Dewine is running against the former director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau Richard Cordray to become governor of Ohio. Cordray is a registered Democrat and was endorsed by Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D-Mass.).
